  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Federal contract obligations in Alaska totaled $2.8B in FY2026 to date, distributed across 7,305 awards with an average award size of $379K. Obligations fell 28.1% year over year. Year-to-year historical totals show FY21 at $2.3B, FY22 at $3.3B, FY23 at $3.8B, FY24 at $3.8B, and FY25 at $3.8B. The Department of Defense accounted for $1B of FY2026 to date obligations, followed by the Department of Homeland Security at $537M and the General Services Administration at $480M. The largest single vendor obligation was DAVIS CONSTRUCTORS & ENGINEERS, INC. with $464M, and other top vendors include TRIWEST HEALTHCARE ALLIANCE CORP at $227M and TUTOR PERINI CORPORATION at $225M. Construction-related spending is the largest industry share, with Commercial and Institutional Building Construction at $929M. The data are partial (fiscal year to date) and reflect obligations rather than completed payments or contract values.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "What changed in FY2026 to date compared with prior years?",
        "body": "Obligations in FY2026 to date are $2.8B, down 28.1% year over year from the prior fiscal period. The FY2026 to date total contrasts with FY25, FY24, and FY23, each at $3.8B, and with FY22 at $3.3B and FY21 at $2.3B. The decline appears alongside a lower aggregate than the three consecutive $3.8B years."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies, vendors, and industries are largest in FY2026 to date?",
        "body": "The top buying agency is the Department of Defense at $1B, followed by the Department of Homeland Security at $537M and the General Services Administration at $480M. The top vendor is DAVIS CONSTRUCTORS & ENGINEERS, INC. at $464M, with TRIWEST HEALTHCARE ALLIANCE CORP at $227M and TUTOR PERINI CORPORATION at $225M. Commercial and Institutional Building Construction leads industries at $929M, followed by Pharmacy Benefit Management at $227M and Facilities Support Services at $180M."
      }
    ]
  },
